reviews.review_text: Fire on Fire!! I think some of these Scarlet>Fires from '80 rival the best from '77 and this one is right up there.  The Scarlet is nice as is the transition but the Fire is a killer with Jerry just letting loose at the end.  Jack Straw is a nice first set closer and the Estimated>Eyes is fantastic.  Definitely worth a listen.

Althea Jack Straw To End First Set! The Althea from this show is really hot, especially the lead before the last verse.  The hot Althea sets up the unusual Jack Straw set closer which they took advantage of by playing a great second lead.  It has always been one of my favorite Jack Straws.
Nice Setlist and Performance This is nice effort that will be enjoyed by the '80's aficionado.  Nothing really standout, but no major glitches or shwag tunes...

A WEEK BEFORE LEWISTON So, these guys had taped the show, and instantly replayed it in the lot, and i had never seen spinning freaks, quite like that fashion in a trance ... THE TAPE WAS BEING PLAYED OUT OF AN OLD VAN (MAYBE A FORD, MAYBE A CHEVY, MAYBE A DODGE) ... with the side doors open ... and it was basically the same MOMENTS being played over again (with parts of the original audience) ... just LOVING IT AS MUCH AS THE FIRST TIME ... THEY ALL LOOKED LIKE JESUS, OR JOHN LENNON (AND HE WAS STILL ALIVE THAT EVENING) ... i must say it was fun to be part of that experience that evening ...HELL OF A TIME GETTING HOME! ... AND THEN, YES, ON TO LEWISTON!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!
Labor Day Weekend w/ the Boys at the wreck-trum You know this space is getting hot.  Labor Day weekend in the City of Brotherly Love . 1980 Brent melding with Jerry. ....so good
